3:
They do not do things that are wrong;
\q2 they behave as Yahweh wants them to.
\q1

8:
I will obey all your statutes;
\q2 do not desert me!
\q1

9:
I know how a young person can live in a pure way;
\q2 it is by obeying your commands.
\q1

10:
I try to serve you with my entire inner being;
\q2 do not allow me to wander away from what you have commanded.
\q1

12:
Yahweh, I praise you;
\q2 teach me your statutes.
\q1

14:
I delight in obeying your requirements;
\q1 I enjoy that more than being very rich.
\q1

19:
I am living here on the earth for only a short time;
\q2 do not keep me from understanding.
\q1

21:
You rebuke those who are proud;
\q2 you curse those who disobey your commands.
\q1

22:
Do not allow them to continue to insult and scorn me;
\q2 I request this because I have obeyed your requirements.
\q1

25:
I think that I will soon die;
\q2 save my life as you have promised me that you would.
\q1

26:
When I told you about all the things I did, you answered me;
\q2 teach me your statutes.
\q1

28:
I am very sad, with the result that I have no strength;
\q2 enable me to be strong again as you promised me that you would do.
\q1

30:
I have decided that I will faithfully obey you;
\q2 I am determined to follow your commands.
\q1

31:
Yahweh, I try to carefully cling to your requirements;
\q2 do not abandon me or let me be disgraced.
\q1

37:
Do not allow me to look at things that are worthless;
\q2 make me able to live as you want me to live.
\q1

50:
When I have been suffering, you comforted me;
\q2 you did what you promised me, and that kept me alive.
\q1

58:
With all my inner being I plead with you to be good to me;
\q2 act kindly to me as you promised that you would do.
\q1

68:
You are very good, and what you do is good;
\q2 teach me your statutes.
\q1

73:
You created me and formed my body;
\q2 help me to be wise so that I may learn your commands.
\q1

78:
Cause the proud people who falsely accuse me to be shamed;
\q2 but as for me, I will continue meditating on what you have commanded I should do.
\q1

81:
I am waiting for you to save me from my enemies;
\q2 I confidently expect that you will tell me what you will do.
\q1

86:
All your commands are trustworthy;
\q2 but people are persecuting me by telling lies about me, so please help me.
\q1

89:
Yahweh, your word will last forever;
\q2 it is firmly fixed in heaven.
\q1

90:
You will faithfully continue to act for people who are not yet born;
\q2 you have put the earth in its place, and it remains firmly there.
\q1

91:
To this day, all things on the earth remain because you decided that they should remain;
\q2 everything on the earth serves you.
\q1

105:
Your word is a lamp to guide me;
\q2 it is like a light that shows me where to walk. 
\q1

107:
Yahweh, I am suffering very much;
\q2 cause me to be strong again as you have promised to do.
\q1

111:
I have your requirements forever;
\q2 because of them, I am joyful in my inner being.
\q1

118:
You reject all those who disobey your statutes;
\q2 because they make deceitful plans and they do not keep their word.
\q1

119:
You get rid of all the wicked people on the earth as people get rid of trash;
\q2 therefore I love your requirements.
\q1

121:
But I have done what is right and fair;
\q2 so do not allow people to oppress me.
\q1

127:
Truly, I love your commands more than I love gold;
\q2 I love them more than I love very pure gold.
\q1

133:
Guide me as you promised;
\q2 do not allow evil people to control what I do.
\q1

145:
Yahweh, with all my inner being I call out to you;
\q2 answer me and I will obey your statutes.
\q1

147:
Each morning I arise before dawn and call to you to help me;
\q2 I confidently expect you to do what you have promised.
\q1

150:
Those evil people who oppress me are coming closer to me;
\q2 they do not pay any attention to your laws.
\q1

154:
Defend me when others accuse me and rescue me from them;
\q2 allow me to continue to live as you promised that you would.
\q1

156:
Yahweh, you have been merciful by helping me in many ways;
\q2 allow me to continue to live as you have done until now.
\q1

159:
Yahweh, notice that I love your principles of behavior;
\q2 because you faithfully love me, allow me to continue to live.
\q1

165:
Things go well for those who love your laws;
\q2 nothing will make them abandon your laws.
\q1

167:
I obey what you require us to do;
\q2 I love it all very much.
\q1

169:
Yahweh, listen while I pray for you to help me;
\q2 help me to understand your words.
\q1

174:
Yahweh, I eagerly desire for you to rescue me from my enemies;
\q2 I am delighted with your laws.
\q1
